---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Thread Taxonomy"
  description="Failure modes in email and Teams threads — and how to counteract them quietly."
>
  <article id="thread-taxonomy">
    <header>
      <h1>Thread Taxonomy</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        How to reduce entropy in corporate communication without being appointed
        manager.
      </p>

      <aside
        class="provenance-note"
        role="note"
        aria-label="Authorship and provenance note"
      >
        <span class="provenance-label">AI-generated text</span>
        <span class="provenance-text"
          >Drafted with an AI system. Reviewed and edited by a human.</span
        >
      </aside>
    </header>

    <!-- ===================== UNANSWERED ===================== -->

    <section id="cat-unanswered" aria-labelledby="cat-unanswered-heading">
      <h2 id="cat-unanswered-heading">Unanswered</h2>
      <p>
        Questions that receive no clear response. Usually caused by ambiguity,
        overload, or diffusion of responsibility.
      </p>

      <!-- 5/5 -->
      <section
        id="orphaned"
        data-term="orphaned"
        aria-labelledby="orphaned-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="orphaned-heading">Orphaned</h3>
        <p>A direct question receives no reply.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>
            Reply-all, quote the exact question, suggest owner and soft
            deadline.
          </dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>
            Always name a
            <a
              href="https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/people-group/directly-responsible-individuals/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              <abbr title="Directly Responsible Individual">DRI</abbr>
            </a>
            when asking.
          </dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="5" min="0" max="5" title="5/5">5 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Neutral tone. Quote verbatim.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Escalate to explicit decision request or 1:1 key actor.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 5/5 -->
      <section
        id="overlooked"
        data-term="overlooked"
        aria-labelledby="overlooked-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="overlooked-heading">Overlooked</h3>
        <p>Question buried in noise.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Re-ask succinctly. Isolate single question.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>One clear ask per paragraph.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="5" min="0" max="5" title="5/5">5 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Minimal prose.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Start new focused thread.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 4/5 -->
      <section
        id="dangling"
        data-term="dangling"
        aria-labelledby="dangling-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="dangling-heading">Dangling</h3>
        <p>Conversation pauses mid-resolution.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Summarize state and propose concrete next action.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>End threads with explicit next step.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="4" min="0" max="5" title="4/5">4 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Short numbered summary.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Timebox: proceed if no objections.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 3/5 -->
      <section
        id="ghosted"
        data-term="ghosted"
        aria-labelledby="ghosted-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="ghosted-heading">Ghosted</h3>
        <p>Individual disengages silently.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>1:1 check-in. Ask if blocked.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Agree on response norms.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="3" min="0" max="5" title="3/5">3 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Private first. Assume good intent.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Escalate publicly with neutral framing.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>
    </section>

    <!-- ===================== OWNERSHIP ===================== -->

    <section id="cat-ownership" aria-labelledby="cat-ownership-heading">
      <h2 id="cat-ownership-heading">Ownership</h2>
      <p>
        Patterns where responsibility is unclear, diffused, or improperly
        transferred.
      </p>

      <!-- 5/5 -->
      <section
        id="ownerless"
        data-term="ownerless"
        aria-labelledby="ownerless-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="ownerless-heading">Ownerless</h3>
        <p>No clear responsible individual.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Propose specific DRI.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Default to single owner per task.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="5" min="0" max="5" title="5/5">5 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. “Suggest X owns unless objections.”</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Volunteer temporarily and request formal owner.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 4/5 -->
      <section
        id="diffused"
        data-term="diffused"
        aria-labelledby="diffused-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="diffused-heading">Diffused</h3>
        <p>Too many recipients, no actor.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Narrow to 1–2 named individuals.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Avoid broad CC unless informational.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="4" min="0" max="5" title="4/5">4 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Tag specific names.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Restart smaller thread.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 3/5 -->
      <section
        id="delegated"
        data-term="delegated"
        aria-labelledby="delegated-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="delegated-heading">Delegated</h3>
        <p>Task handed off but not accepted.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Request explicit confirmation.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Normalize acknowledgment on delegation.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="3" min="0" max="5" title="3/5">3 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Direct but neutral.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Escalate or reassign.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 3/5 -->
      <section
        id="stranded"
        data-term="stranded"
        aria-labelledby="stranded-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="stranded-heading">Stranded</h3>
        <p>Blocked by absent decision authority.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Frame crisp decision question.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Clarify decision rights early.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="3" min="0" max="5" title="3/5">3 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Options-based framing.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Escalate with summary + impact.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>
    </section>

    <!-- ===================== SIGNAL ===================== -->

    <section id="cat-signal" aria-labelledby="cat-signal-heading">
      <h2 id="cat-signal-heading">Signal</h2>
      <p>
        Structural problems in clarity, focus, and information flow within a
        thread.
      </p>

      <!-- 4/5 -->
      <section id="buried" data-term="buried" aria-labelledby="buried-heading">
        <h3 id="buried-heading">Buried</h3>
        <p>Key issue lost in long thread.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Extract to new focused thread.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Single-topic discipline.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="4" min="0" max="5" title="4/5">4 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Announce new thread for clarity.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Close old thread explicitly.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 4/5 -->
      <section
        id="underspecified"
        data-term="underspecified"
        aria-labelledby="underspecified-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="underspecified-heading">Underspecified</h3>
        <p>Missing details block action.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Request minimal checklist info.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Use structured templates.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="4" min="0" max="5" title="4/5">4 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Neutral, factual gaps.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Propose assumptions and proceed unless corrected.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 3/5 -->
      <section
        id="fragmented"
        data-term="fragmented"
        aria-labelledby="fragmented-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="fragmented-heading">Fragmented</h3>
        <p>Context split across tools or threads.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Consolidate and link canonical source.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Maintain single source of truth.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="3" min="0" max="5" title="3/5">3 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Reference summary doc.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Create short recap and anchor future discussion.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 3/5 -->
      <section
        id="hijacked"
        data-term="hijacked"
        aria-labelledby="hijacked-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="hijacked-heading">Hijacked</h3>
        <p>Thread drifts away from original topic.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Suggest splitting topic.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Subject-line discipline.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="3" min="0" max="5" title="3/5">3 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Polite redirect.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Hard split into new thread.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>
    </section>

    <!-- ===================== BEHAVIOR ===================== -->

    <section id="cat-behavior" aria-labelledby="cat-behavior-heading">
      <h2 id="cat-behavior-heading">Behavior</h2>
      <p>
        Interaction patterns that reduce clarity or accountability without
        necessarily being malicious.
      </p>

      <!-- 4/5 -->
      <section id="vague" data-term="vague" aria-labelledby="vague-heading">
        <h3 id="vague-heading">Vague</h3>
        <p>Non-actionable phrasing.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Translate to concrete proposal.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Encourage problem + proposal norm.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="4" min="0" max="5" title="4/5">4 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. “Do you mean X?”</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Offer two specific interpretations.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 3/5 -->
      <section
        id="driveby"
        data-term="driveby"
        aria-labelledby="driveby-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="driveby-heading">Driveby</h3>
        <p>Comment without ownership.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Ask who will take it.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Pair comments with owners.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="3" min="0" max="5" title="3/5">3 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Curious tone.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Assign provisional owner.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>
    </section>

    <!-- ===================== DECISION ===================== -->

    <section id="cat-decision" aria-labelledby="cat-decision-heading">
      <h2 id="cat-decision-heading">Decision</h2>
      <p>
        Patterns where agreement, authority, or closure is missing or unstable.
      </p>

      <!-- 4/5 -->
      <section
        id="nonbinding"
        data-term="nonbinding"
        aria-labelledby="nonbinding-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="nonbinding-heading">Nonbinding</h3>
        <p>Agreement not formally recorded.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Summarize decision + owner/date.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Maintain decision log.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="4" min="0" max="5" title="4/5">4 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public recap.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Log in shared tracker.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 4/5 -->
      <section
        id="untracked"
        data-term="untracked"
        aria-labelledby="untracked-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="untracked-heading">Untracked</h3>
        <p>No follow-up mechanism exists.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Add to tracker and link.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Visible task board.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="4" min="0" max="5" title="4/5">4 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Transparent tracking.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Escalate missed deadline with data.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 3/5 -->
      <section
        id="indecisive"
        data-term="indecisive"
        aria-labelledby="indecisive-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="indecisive-heading">Indecisive</h3>
        <p>Endless analysis without closure.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Present two options + decision date.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Timebox decisions.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="3" min="0" max="5" title="3/5">3 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public. Structured options.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Default decision after deadline.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- 2/5 -->
      <section
        id="reopened"
        data-term="reopened"
        aria-labelledby="reopened-heading"
      >
        <h3 id="reopened-heading">Reopened</h3>
        <p>Closed issue repeatedly revived.</p>
        <dl>
          <dt>Next step</dt>
          <dd>Reference prior rationale.</dd>
          <dt>Prevention</dt>
          <dd>Keep decisions visible.</dd>
          <dt>Commonality</dt>
          <dd>
            <meter value="2" min="0" max="5" title="2/5">2 out of 5</meter>
          </dd>
          <dt>Channel</dt>
          <dd>Public, factual.</dd>
          <dt>If next step fails</dt>
          <dd>Ask for new evidence or close thread.</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>
    </section>

    <footer>
      <p class="text-muted">
        Leadership without title is mostly about reducing ambiguity.
      </p>

      <nav aria-label="Related pages">
        <p class="text-muted">See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="/ai-generated/ambient-improvement-positive-residue"
              >Ambient Improvement</a
            > — the same quiet discipline applied to code
          </li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Layout>
